<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">

    <!-- Title of the page. This shows up on the browser tab and clearly identifies the app as Workit.-->
    <title>Workit - Home</title>

    <!--  Linking to my main CSS file. The path /css/styles.css works because Express serves the /public folder as static files. -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/styles.css">
</head>

<body>

<!-- header section: This is the top section of my page. It includes: My Workit logo image, The site name, Navigation links to the rest of the app-->
<header class="header">

    <!-- LOGO and SITE NAME: I’m grouping the logo image and the Workit title together so they appear as one unit.-->
    <div class="logo">
        <!-- Custom Workit logo image that I created. The file is stored in /public/images as logo-workit.PNG.-->
        <img src="/images/logo-workit.PNG" alt="Workit Logo" class="logo-img">

        <!-- Main site name that the user sees on every page. -->
        <h1 class="site-name">Workit</h1>
    </div>

    <!-- navigation bar: These links connect the landing page to the other main parts of the app.Home (this page), Add Workout (Create), My Workouts (Read/Update/Delete handled by the other pages)-->
    <nav class="nav">
        <!-- Link that brings the user back to the landing page. -->
        <a href="/" class="nav-link">Home</a>

        <!-- Link to the Add Workout page. This is where the user will create a new workout entry.-->
        <a href="/workouts/new" class="nav-link">Add Workout</a>

        <!-- Link to the My Workouts page. This will show a list of all workouts so the user can manage them.-->
        <a href="/workouts" class="nav-link">My Workouts</a>
    </nav>
</header>

<!-- hero section: This is the main part of the landing page. It explains what Workit is and gives the user a clear call-to-action.-->
<main class="hero">
    <!--  Main headline for the home page. I’m using this to quickly communicate the purpose of the app.-->
    <h2>Your Fitness. Your Progress. Your Way.</h2>

    <!-- Description / "About" style text. This is basically our company/app introduction explaining what Workit does in simple language, which matches the assignment requirement for a short description.-->
    <p class="description">
        Workit helps you track workouts, stay consistent, and see your progress.
        It is a simple fitness tracker built to support your health goals.
    </p>

    <!-- hero button: This is the main call-to-action button on the page. When the user clicks this, they go directly to the Add Workout page,where a new workout object will be created.This button is my "hero button that leads to creating a new workout" from the assignment.-->
    <a href="/workouts/new" class="btn hero-btn">Add New Workout</a>
</main>

<!-- footer section: Simple footer with the year and course info. This helps make the page feel complete and also shows that this is for my INFR3120 project.-->
<footer>
    <p>&copy; 2025 Workit · INFR3120 Project</p>
</footer>

</body>
</html>
